    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "AAAAdn//bU8\u003d",
        "filename": "src/dsp/upsampling_mips_dsp_r2.c",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 53,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000898
      },
      "writtenOn": "2014-08-18T15:37:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "on the contrary, the \"do {...} while (0)\" is useful for scoping.\n\n#define YUV_TO_RGB(y,u,v,r,g,b) do { \\\n  int t1, t2, t3,...;\n  ...\n}\n\nand later:\n\nint r,g,b;\nYUV_TO_RGB(y,u,v,r,g,b);\n\nat call site. You still need externally visible r,g,b variables, but the other ones (t1..t5) are local under the \"do{} while(0)\" scope.",
      "parentUuid": "AAAAdn//bVE\u003d",
      "revId": "5f0f40399c307842a00220f5bc14e4a19eecdc0b",
